{{short description|2016 non-fiction book by Gary Younge}} {{Use mdy dates|date=January 2017}} {{Use American English|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox book | name = Another Day in the Death of America | author = [[Gary Younge]] | image = Another Day in the Death of America.jpg | language = English | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | subject = Violence in society, [[social policy]] | published = 2016 ([[The Nation Institute|Nation Books]]) | pages = 267 pp. | isbn = 978-1-56858-975-6 }}
'''''Another Day in the Death of America: A Chronicle of Ten Short Lives''''' is a 2016 non-fiction book by [[Gary Younge]] about 10 American children and teenagers killed by guns in a 24-hour timespan.<ref>[https://theintercept.com/2016/12/18/how-many-children-were-shot-dead-today-an-interview-with-gary-younge/ Theintercept.com]</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/28/books/review-another-day-in-the-death-of-america-on-guns-killing-children.html?_r=0 The New York Times]</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/sep/26/another-day-in-the-death-america-gary-younge-review The Guardian]</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/oct/14/another-day-in-the-death-of-america-gary-younge-review-usa-gun-culture The Guardian]</ref><ref>[https://www.ft.com/content/deede2c4-84a6-11e6-8897-2359a58ac7a5 Ft.com]</ref><ref>[http://www.theroot.com/articles/culture/2016/10/the-story-of-10-young-people-killed-in-a-day-by-guns-should-make-you-rethink-american-gun-culture/ The Root]</ref><ref>[http://ew.com/article/2016/10/06/gary-youngs-another-day-death-america-ew-review/ Entertainment Weekly]</ref><ref>[https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/gary-younge/another-day-in-the-death-of-america/ Kirkus Reviews]</ref><ref>[http://blogs.lse.ac.uk/lsereviewofbooks/2016/11/08/book-review-another-day-in-the-death-of-america-a-chronicle-of-ten-short-lives-by-gary-younge/ Lse.ac.uk]</ref><ref>[http://www.spectator.co.uk/2016/09/the-american-way-of-murder-investigating-the-deaths-of-children-and-teenagers-in-the-usa/ Spectator.co.uk]</ref>
Younge explores how the deaths are normal by American standards—in that none made national news—but not normal by civilized standards. It was published by [[The Nation Institute|Nation Books]].
[[David Oyelowo]] will star in the film adaptation of the book.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/apr/14/david-oyelowo-film-adaptation-gary-younge-another-day-in-the-death-of-america The Guardian]</ref>
